sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the S&P 500 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Red Hat Inc (Symbol: RHT), where a total volume of 52,674 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 5.3 million underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 278.7% of RHT's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 1.9 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $190 strike call option expiring January 17, 2020 , with 3,023 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 302,300 underlying shares of RHT.

Moody's Corp. (Symbol: MCO) saw options trading volume of 11,322 contracts, representing approximately 1.1 million underlying shares or approximately 86.3% of MCO's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 1.3 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $155 strike call option expiring November 16, 2018 , with 4,016 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 401,600 underlying shares of MCO.

And Procter & Gamble Company (Symbol: PG) saw options trading volume of 53,870 contracts, representing approximately 5.4 million underlying shares or approximately 46.1% of PG's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 11.7 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $95 strike call option expiring April 18, 2019 , with 20,177 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 2.0 million underlying shares of PG.
